  "prompt": "What is the best clinic for systemic Lupus in United States?",
  "response": "Determining the \"best\" clinic for systemic lupus erythematosus (SLE) can be subjective, as it often depends on individual needs, the severity of the condition, insurance coverage, and geographic location. However, several institutions in the United States are renowned for their expertise in treating autoimmune diseases like lupus:\n\n1. **Mayo Clinic** (Rochester, Minnesota) - Known for its comprehensive and multidisciplinary approach to healthcare, the Mayo Clinic often ranks highly for rheumatology and treatment of autoimmune disorders.\n\n2. **Cleveland Clinic** (Cleveland, Ohio) - Renowned for its research and treatment of lupus, the Cleveland Clinic has a dedicated Center for Vasculitis Care and Research, which specializes in autoimmune and inflammatory disorders.\n\n3. **Johns Hopkins Lupus Center** (Baltimore, Maryland) - Part of the Johns Hopkins University, the Lupus Center is recognized for its research and treatment of lupus and other autoimmune diseases.\n\n4. **Hospital for Special Surgery (HSS)** (New York City, New York) - Known for its rheumatology department, HSS is a leader in the treatment of musculoskeletal and autoimmune conditions.\n\n5. **UCLA Medical Center** (Los Angeles, California) - Their Rheumatology Division is involved in cutting-edge research and offers comprehensive care for lupus patients.\n\n6. **Brigham and Women\u2019s Hospital** (Boston, Massachusetts) - Part of the Harvard Medical School consortium, it has a strong rheumatology division with a focus on autoimmune diseases.\n\nWhen choosing a clinic or specialist, consider consulting with your primary care physician or current rheumatologist. They can provide referrals based on your specific health needs. Additionally, checking with your insurance provider to understand coverage options is also important.",
